---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Philosophy — Meish"
  description="Meish measures what others do not dare to measure. We make the invisible architecture of human experience visible, so it can be protected and improved."
>
  <section class="section container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Philosophy</p>
    <h1>Meish measures what others do not dare to measure.</h1>
    <p class="lead">Every space, every stay, every journey changes how a person feels —
      whether anyone designed it to or not. Meish makes that invisible architecture visible,
      so it can be protected and improved.</p>

    <h2>The shift we care about</h2>
    <p>A guest is not buying a room, a meal, or a seat. They're buying a change of state:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>from load → recovery</li>
      <li>from hurry → calm</li>
      <li>from ordinary → memorable</li>
      <li>from uncertainty → safety</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Most metrics miss this. Cleanliness scores and speed-of-service tell you what happened
      to the process. Meish tells you what happened in the person — did presence stay
      unbroken, did the body settle, was there afterglow after they left.</p>

    <h2>What we believe</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Every experience is designed</strong> — intentionally or by accident. We choose intention.</li>
      <li><strong>Make the priceless visible without flattening it.</strong> Measuring wonder shouldn't kill it.</li>
      <li><strong>Better experiences should require less unnecessary effort</strong>, not more — for guests and staff alike.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What this is not</h2>
    <p>Not surveillance. Not staff scoring. Not mystery shopping as the main frame. Not a
      quality manual. See our <a href="/privacy">boundaries</a> — trust is the product.</p>

    <p><a class="button button--primary" href="/services">See how it becomes a service</a></p>
  </section>
</Base>
